        <abstract> 
<p>Grateful for CD’s commendation of his Glen Roy paper ["Parallel roads of Glen Roy", <hi rend="italic">Q. J. Geol. Soc. Lond.</hi> 19 (1863): 235–59].</p>  
<p>Reading Justus Liebig [trans. William Gregory, <hi rend="italic">Animal chemistry or organic chemistry</hi> (1842)] has suggested that pattern of evolutionary succession might depend on differential need for soil minerals.</p> 
        </abstract>
